programme.desc: Young architect Richard Hawkes and his wife Sophie have decided to move out of London to live the good life in the Kent countryside. They buy a plot of land on which they plan to grow their own food, and lead as sustainable a life as possible. For Richard it's an opportunity to experiment and build the house of his dreams; one that embraces cutting-edge green technologies and is capable of providing almost all its own energy. He also wants their new home to blend effortlessly into the surrounding countryside, so he decides to build a huge arch from clay tiles, covered with earth and planted with grass: a man-made hill. His new home will nestle out of sight under the arch and also utilise the space the arch creates. He has never built anything like this before and neither has anyone else who is working on it. It may be a great chance for an architect to experiment, but not so much fun for Sophie, who becomes pregnant, gives birth and ends up bringing up the baby in a caravan on site. programme.title: Grand Designs
programme.desc: Young architect Richard Hawkes and his wife Sophie have decided to move out of London to live the good life in the Kent countryside. They buy a plot of land on which they plan to grow their own food, and lead as sustainable a life as possible. For Richard it's an opportunity to experiment and build the house of his dreams; one that embraces cutting-edge green technologies and is capable of providing almost all its own energy. He also wants their new home to blend effortlessly into the surrounding countryside, so he decides to build a huge arch from clay tiles, covered with earth and planted with grass: a man-made hill. His new home will nestle out of sight under the arch and also utilise the space the arch creates. He has never built anything like this before and neither has anyone else who is working on it. It may be a great chance for an architect to experiment, but not so much fun for Sophie, who becomes pregnant, gives birth and ends up bringing up the baby in a caravan on site. Presented by Kevin McCloud(c)
